    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Pat your <strong>duck breast[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then using a sharp knife, score the <strong>duck skin</strong> on a diagonal, being careful not to cut through to the meat</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>scored duck</strong> to the pan, skin-side down and cook for 3-4 min on each side, or until golden</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cherry-hoisin-duck-and-rice-with-sesame-crisp-smacked-cucumber/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rinse your <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a <strong>sieve </strong>under<strong> cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cherry-hoisin-duck-and-rice-with-sesame-crisp-smacked-cucumber/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained rice</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cherry-hoisin-duck-and-rice-with-sesame-crisp-smacked-cucumber/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the duck is golden, transfer the <strong>golden duck</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and reserve the pan</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 10-12 min further or until the duck is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>roast duck</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cherry-hoisin-duck-and-rice-with-sesame-crisp-smacked-cucumber/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the duck is cooking, bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it into large, bite-sized pieces \u2013 this is your <strong>smacked cucumber</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cherry-hoisin-duck-and-rice-with-sesame-crisp-smacked-cucumber/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 2 min or until golden and crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy garlic oil</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>crispy onions</strong> in a large heat-proof bowl, then add the <strong>crispy garlic oil </strong>(reserve the pan!)<strong> </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>sesame crisp</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cherry-hoisin-duck-and-rice-with-sesame-crisp-smacked-cucumber/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the duck is ready, transfer the <strong>roasted duck</strong> to a clean chopping board to rest for 2-3 min</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>ketjap manis</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> cherry sauce </strong>and <strong>hoisin sauce </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened and glossy \u2013 this is your <strong>cherry hoisin</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>smacked cucumber </strong>to the<strong> sesame crisp </strong>and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame crisp smacked cucumber</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cherry-hoisin-duck-and-rice-with-sesame-crisp-smacked-cucumber/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested duck</strong> finely, on the diagonal</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced duck</strong> and drizzle over the <strong>cherry hoisin</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>cooked rice </strong>and<strong> sesame crisp smacked cucumber </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
